hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a function $f$ defined on the interval $[0, 3]$ as follows:
$$
f(x) = \begin{cases}
x^2 & \text{if } x \in [0, 3] \text{ and } x \neq \sqrt{2} \\
0 & \text{if } x = \sqrt{2}
\end{cases}
$$
Calculate the lower Darboux integral $L(f)$ and the upper Darboux integral $U(f)$ of the function $f$ over the interval $[0, 3]$.

Express your answer as a pair of values, $(L(f), U(f))$, in the format of a row matrix.
